Avoid any SPOF.
Decompose workload per different SLA.
Minimize and understand service dependencies.
Design tasks and messages to be idempotent where possible.
Use a message broker that implements high availability for critical transactions.
Design applications to gracefully degrade.
Gracefully handle rapid burst events.
Host applications in multiple datacenters.
Automate and test deployment and maintenance tasks.
Take advantage of data replication through both local and geographical redundancy.
Use optimistic concurrency and eventual consistency where possible.
Use periodic backup and point-in-time restore.
Fall back to a different service or workflow where possible.
Plan for disaster recovery.
